Description:
Sheffield City Council's (SCC) Transport & Facilities Management and Capital Delivery Service teams commission a large number of maintenance and refurbishment projects across the estate each year. Such projects, in older buildings have a risk of asbestos. It is therefore necessary to commission the services of asbestos professionals to identify and manage the removal of ACMs on a regular basis. 

Existing arrangements involve the ad-hoc procurement of:
• Management and R&D Surveys; 
• Asbestos Project Management of removals/abatements and Analytical services. 

SCCs objective is to establish a Term Contract with 2nr Consultants for the provision of all asbestos consultancy related services in order to deliver the following:
• Efficiencies in procurement; 
• Reduction in programme for appointment of consultant and completion of surveys; 
•	 Develop working relationship with a consultant to ensure documentation and standards regularly meet SCC requirements;
• Put in place a contingency fund to facilitate emergency asbestos removals (via the Term Contract).

Parking Services are now looking to acquire 40 body worn video cameras for the Civil Enforcement Officers to wear whilst carrying out their duties. 

These are required to improve the following:- 
Increase public reassurance; 
Reduce fear of crime in local communities; 
Increase early guilty pleas; 
Resolve complaints about Civil Enforcement Officers more quickly; Reduce assaults and threats on Civil Enforcement Officers
